## Why Asked
Assesses conflict resolution, negotiation skills, and ability to maintain team harmony while achieving project goals.
## Key Concepts
Active listening, mediation techniques, finding win-win solutions, maintaining professional relationships.
## Code Example
```
// Example of mediating technical disagreement:
function resolveConflict(dev1, dev2, requirements) {
  const commonGoals = findIntersection(dev1.goals, dev2.goals);
  const compromise = createSolution(commonGoals, requirements);
  return compromise;
}
```
## Follow-up Questions
How did you ensure both parties felt heard? What if no compromise was possible? How do you handle similar situations now?

## Why This Is Asked
Coinbase needs engineers who can make high-stakes decisions under uncertainty, balancing technical risks with business continuity. This tests judgment, risk assessment, and communication skills.

## Expected Answer
Strong candidates describe: 1) Clear production context, 2) Specific incomplete data points, 3) Decision framework used, 4) Risk mitigation strategy, 5) Measurable outcomes, 6) Lessons learned.

## Code Example
```typescript
// Risk assessment framework used
class ProductionDecision {
  assessRisk(impact: number, probability: number, dataConfidence: number): number {
    return impact * probability * (1 - dataConfidence);
  }

  shouldProceed(riskScore: number, threshold: number): boolean {
    return riskScore < threshold;
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle stakeholder disagreement on your decision?
- What monitoring would you implement to validate your choice?
- When would you decide to rollback vs. continue?

## Why This Is Asked
IBM wants to see how you handle change management, influence without authority, and drive technical decisions through data and collaboration rather than just technical expertise.

## Expected Answer
A strong candidate will describe: 1) A specific technical challenge or opportunity, 2) How they gathered data/evidence to support their proposal, 3) How they addressed team concerns through demos or proof-of-concepts, 4) The measurable business impact of the change.

## Code Example
```typescript
// Example: Converting team to TypeScript
interface LegacyAPI {
  data: any;
  status: number;
}

// Proposed typed approach
interface TypedAPI<T> {
  data: T;
  status: number;
  error?: string;
}

// Proof of concept showing type safety
function processResponse<T>(response: TypedAPI<T>): T | null {
  if (response.status === 200 && response.data) {
    return response.data;
  }
  return null;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle this situation if you were the most junior person on the team?
- What metrics would you use to measure the success of the technology adoption?
- How do you balance innovation with maintaining system stability?
